!FIRST and most important: you need a STATIC LIGHTNING NETWORK ADDRESS!
Many wallet support #zaps now, but many are Custiodial, so do not leave too many funds in there.
Do your own research and understand the trade offs of having one, like WalletOfSatoshi for example, probably the easiset to use.
Nip57(zap) compatible HOSTED wallets: WoS, BitcoinJungle, Strike, ln.tips, BitcoinBeach, Current (client+walet), Zebedee, Alby, AnonSats.
Nip57(zap) compatible wallets: nostdress, BTCPay Server

- You have STRIKE? Super easy, just put " YourUsername@strike.army " in your profile setup URL for lightning and you are zappable!
Here is how you can send and receive âš¡âš¡ Zaps using LNTipBot made by @calle :
-First click here: https://t.me/LightningTipBot 
Set it up and copy / paste your LN address in your Nostr profile. 
-NIP-57 support? In the telegram channel with the bot type: /nostr add <your_pubkey>
Want to link the tipbot with BlueWallet or Zeus? 
- Type /link in the Telegram bot channel after having it setup. Scan the QR in BlueWallet -> import wallet or Zeus LndHub.
- Enter /link in LightningTipBot, go to Zeus, add new LndHub wallet, scan QR code and you're in. 
- Link also possible with Alby from desktop, just import new LndHub
 
If you want the zaps to appear under your posts:
- Go to LightningTipBot. Enter "/help" if you don't know your Lightning address.
- See your address? Mine is intuitiveguy@ln.tips
- Optional: Enter "/advanced" to get an anonymous address if you don't want to doxx your Telegram username.
- Put your Lightning address into your nostr profile
- In LightningTipBot, register your nostr pubkey with "/nostr add <your_pubkey>"
- You're done! You'll receive zaps and they will be shown under your zapped posts! âš¡âš¡
